Vision (David Bowie Tribute)","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Paying tribute to David Bowie? For BowieVision, it's not a one-time proposition, it's a way of life. 

In the wake of Bowie’s grand exit, the musical mission the band undertook more than two years ago has taken on a deeper significance and an increased urgency. Bowie fans are clamoring to hear the songs that hold so much meaning for them performed live by a band that shares their sincere love and respect for the man and his music. 

Bowie lit the flame, and BowieVision is proud to carry the torch.

Combining deft musicianship, masterful stage presence, and stunning video and lighting effects, the BowieVision experience is simultaneously epic and intimate, an approach that resonates with audiences on a more profound level than mere impersonation ever could. BowieVision consistently draws sell-out crowds to premiere venues like Seattle’s Crocodile, Triple Door, Tractor Tavern, and Nectar Lounge. 

The band has the rare ability to do justice to nearly every phase of Bowie’s eclectic career, delivering rock anthems like Rebel Rebel, All the Young Dudes, and Suffragette City; the wide-screen balladry of Life on Mars?, Space Oddity, and Changes; mid-70s “plastic soul” (Golden Years, Young Americans, Fame;) art-pop statements like Fashion, Heroes, Ashes to Ashes, and I’m Afraid of Americans; and the high-sheen Eighties classics Under Pressure, Let’s Dance, China Girl, and Blue Jean.

BowieVision sold out at Doug Fir twice in 2015, and this show will undoubtedly follow suit, so get your tickets now.

Here’s a sampling of what the press has to say about BowieVision: 

“Seattle's BowieVision reinterprets the classic works of David Bowie—and does so with a phenomenal amount of verve and charm.” 

—		Erik Henriksen, Portland Mercury, 7/25/15

“The band performs all of Bowie's hits and some of his more obscure numbers with a fierce energy that keeps the audience entertained and delighted. …An opportunity to experience David Bowie's music live from a group that can deliver it with fullness and passion. The overall experience of BowieVision was a David Bowie full meal deal well worth any fan's attention.”

—	Steven Sieden, Huffpost  6/8/15

“…One-ups the traditional tribute-band formula with a projected video backdrop as part of the show…a hell of a night for Bowie diehards.”

—	Mike Ramos, The Stranger
